The paper focuses on scene text detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The proposed algorithm also involves the use of a Fully Convolutional Network (FCN) model, which is a popular deep learning technique, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of semantic segmentation, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR), suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with text analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP), indicating that cs.CL (Computation and Language) may also be a possible category.
